\f0\fs24 \cf2 \cb3 1. The Problem (In Plain English)\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f1\fs21 \cf2 \cb3 India has hundreds of government welfare schemes \'97 PM Kisan (cash for farmers), PMAY (housing), Ayushman Bharat (health insurance), etc. The official details live inside dense PDF documents full of legal language, tables, and eligibility criteria.\cb1 \
\cb3 The real-world pain:\cb1 \
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls1\ilvl0\cf2 \cb3 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
A farmer in Maharashtra wants to know:\'a0
\f2\i "Am I eligible for PM Kisan?"
\f1\i0 \cb1 \
\ls1\ilvl0\cb3 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
To find out, they'd need to download a 30-page PDF, read through it, and interpret bureaucratic language.\cb1 \
\ls1\ilvl0\cb3 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Most people give up, or rely on middlemen who may give wrong information.\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \cb3 Your solution:\'a0Build a chatbot where anyone types a question in plain English and gets an accurate answer\'a0
\f2\i pulled directly from the official document
\f1\i0 \'a0\'97 not from the internet, not hallucinated, but from the actual PDF.\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \cb4 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa120\partightenfactor0

