\f0 \cf2 \cb3 Why not just give the whole PDF to the AI?\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f1 \cf2 \cb3 Three reasons:\cb1 \
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls2\ilvl0\cf2 \cb3 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	1	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Token limits\'a0\'97 GPT-4o-mini can handle ~128K tokens, but a large PDF could exceed that\cb1 \
\ls2\ilvl0\cb3 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	2	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Cost\'a0\'97 You pay per token. Sending the entire PDF with every question = expensive\cb1 \
\ls2\ilvl0\cb3 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	3	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Accuracy\'a0\'97 The more irrelevant text you send, the more likely the AI is to get confused or hallucinate\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa60\partightenfactor0

